e-TEF / e-TEF Canada / e-TEFaQ


     __________________________________________________________________

   The official e-TEF Canada and e-TEFaQ are now offered at ILSC-Montréal
   and ILSC-Toronto.

What is the e-TEF Canada and the e-TEFaQ?

   The Test d’Évaluation du Français (TEF Canada) and the Test de Français
   adapté au Québec (TEFaQ) are language proficiency tests designed by the
   Chamber of Commerce of Paris Ile-de-France and both are recognized by
   the MICC (Ministère de l’immigration et des Communautés Culturelles du
   Québec) and by the CIC (Citizenship and Immigration Canada).

   Le e-TEF, le e-TEF Canada et le e-TEFaQ sont désormais proposés à
   ILSC-Montréal et ILSC-Toronto.

Qu'est-ce que le e-TEF Canada et le e-TEFaQ?

   Le Test d’Évaluation du Français (TEF Canada) et le Test d’Évaluation
   du Français adapté au Québec (TEFaQ) sont deux tests conçus par la
   Chambre de Commerce de Paris-Île-de-France et sont reconnus par le MICC
   (Ministère de l’immigration et des Communautés Culturelles du
   Québec) et par le CIC (Citoyenneté et Immigration Canada).

   ILSC-TEF is located at:
   443 University Avenue, 3rd Floor, Toronto, ON, M5G 2H6, near St.
   Patrick Station

   Contact: Nasrin K
   Email contact: tef.toronto[at]ilsc[dot]com
   Phone contact: 416 323 1770.

   Nasrin's office hours include:
   Monday, Wednesday and Friday
   13:00h to 17:00h



The Tests



e-TEFaQ

   The TEFaQ has two mandatory parts: oral comprehension and oral
   expression. However, it is possible to add two optional parts: written
   comprehension and written expression.

Oral Comprehension (computer based)

   40 minutes / 60 questions / 360 points

Oral Expression

   15 minutes / 2 subjects / 450 points

   Your oral expression will be assessed through a face-to-face speaking
   test with one assessor.



e-TEF Canada

   4 Parts:
     * Oral Comprehension (computer based)
     * Oral Expression
     * Written Comprehension (computer based)
     * Written Expression


e-TEF

   The TEF has 5 parts:
     * Written Comprehension - 60 questions (computer based)
     * Oral Comprehension - 60 questions (computer based)
     * Lexicon and Structure - 40 questions (computer based)
     * Written Expression - 60 min
     * Oral Expression -  15 min


